Michael Vullis said:
(re: VTeX's support of OpenType and contextual ligatures)
>Handled the "TeX-way". It makes no sense to use the OpenType ligature
>mechanism when TeX does it quite well.

up to the limits of .tfm's 256 character limit. If one is interested in
the idea of using fonts which have more ligatures than that, well, it
makes sense to me.

